public class ObjectListTableModel<T>
extends javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel

TableModel that parses object of type T based on the specified rules and shows each object in a separate rows. Individual properties are shown as cell in the row.

Author:
Branislav Stojkovic

public ObjectListTableModel(java.lang.Class<? extends T> dataClass,

                     throws java.lang.SecurityException,
                            java.lang.NoSuchMethodException
Creates a model based on the specified dataClass and field. Each field may have on of the following syntax forms:
  • getterName - creates a read only field which reads values using the specified getter
  • getterName/setterName - creates an editable field which uses getter to read and setter to write value
  • action:actionName - creates an action column with the specified name
